14/11/2003
WASHINGTON, United States -- Senior foreign policy officials from Albania, Croatia, and Macedonia met Thursday (13 November) within the framework of a US initiative on Adriatic partnership towards NATO membership. 
In a joint appearance at Washington's Woodrow Wilson Centre, Croatian Deputy Foreign Minister Ivan Simonovic, Acting Albanian Foreign Minister Luan Hajdaraga, and Macedonian Foreign Minister Ilinka Mitreva outlined their countries' efforts to meet the requirements for NATO and EU membership. 
They called for the Euro-Atlantic integration of all Balkan countries and pledged to work together to attain this goal. 
(VOA - 13/11/03)
